  "prompt": "On moon men feel lighter weight than earth?",
  "response": "Yes, on the Moon, men (and all objects) feel lighter in weight compared to Earth. This is because the Moon has less gravitational force than Earth. Specifically, the gravitational acceleration on the Moon is about one-sixth that of Earth's. So, if you weigh 100 pounds on Earth, you would weigh approximately 16.6 pounds on the Moon. This reduced gravity makes you feel much lighter.",
